Businessman Hamilton Ndlovu. eNCA\Screenshot JOHANNESBURG - Hamilton Ndlovu and his companies have been ordered to repay R158-million. He acquired the money through a fraudulent COVID-19 PPE contract. Ndlovu made headlines when he flashed a fleet of luxury vehicles on social media. WATCH: Hamilton Ndlovu probed for PPE tender fraud He had unlawfully scored a R172-million contract from the National Health Laboratory Services. eNCA can exclusively reveal the Special Tribunal ordered Ndlovu’s properties and luxury vehicles to be forfeited to the state. Judge Lebogang Modiba handed down judgment electronically on Tuesday.